  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I want to see real size of installed programs.\n### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n*Summary*:  wrong size of Status Desktop is shown in Control Panel > Programs and Features - instead of real size is shown 85,2 GB\n\n#### Expected behavior\nreal size of app\n\n#### Actual behavior\n85,2 GB is shown\n![size](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/49370142-a0cbd980-f6f3-11e8-8a84-4ac30a04d311.png)\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Download and install Status \n- Open Control Panel > Programs > Programs and features\n- Check out Status Desktop size\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: nightly 30/11/2018\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\n* Operating System: Windows 10 home",
